To experience once in your life a hallucination.
Unlike dreams, Fuchs says, "the sensory and spatial structure of reality that is perceived during psychosis is basically preserved".
Delusional thoughts and hallucinations are based on reality, the alienation of the experience takes place in a real setting.
Why our brains do these kinds of freaks is still a mystery to researchers.
According to Fuchs, exceptional situations can cause everyone to lose momentary perception of reality.
