Schmidt-Degenhard studied the so-called oniroid form of experience, a particular form of alteration of consciousness awakened by dreaming.
Oniroid vices are very complex half-dreams that are perceived as real by the person experiencing them and that he cannot differentiate from the dream even when he is awake.
Oniroid awareness occurs during trauma or in extreme conditions, such as in patients with polyradiculopathy who are fully conscious but experience motor paralysis.
