How much should you be paid based on your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can find out what salary they would earn based on their profile, thanks to a new application from Trovit, the search engine with the highest number of small ads for real estate, jobs and vehicles in Spain.
The tool  How much should you be paid?  calculates users' salaries from over 140 000 job vacancies available to Trovit in Spain, using a form available on Facebook, where you must enter your profession, years of experience, age and the city where you want to work.
The search engine has been running for a week and has detected that, as a general rule, Spanish workers feel underpaid, said Trovit's product manager Albert Ribera in a statement.
According to data available to Trovità from its search engines in the UK and France, the Spanish are the least well paid.
A British computer programmer earns €45,226 gross per year, a Frenchman €31,059, while a Spanishman receives €24,000.
Similarly, a driver receives a gross annual salary of €34,247 in England, €25,751 in France and €16,420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid job in Spain is that of waiter, with €11,592 net per year, followed by salesman, with €14,725, and laborer, with €15,667.
The most searched jobs on the Internet in the last three months are driver, part-time and social worker.
