In this area, it considers that an additional 18 000 MW are needed, with additional supporting energy sources.
Galán, who believes that the Sustainable Economy Bill that the government has just approved is in line with his company's demands, did not want to attack the royal decree to encourage national coal consumption, which contradicts policies to combat global warming.
He believes that there is a clear long-term stake in this regard, despite the one-off measures, as described by the Iberdrola president.
