It now intends to consolidate these two areas and to take advantage of synergies to enter the construction and infrastructure management markets.
The underground tollway, promoted by the Brisbane City Infrastructure Office and known as the Northern Link, is designed to link the Western Toowong Highway to the Kelvin Grove bypass (see map), via a 4 km tunnel.
The timetable set by the administration indicates that the tender will take place during the summer of 2010 and that work will start in December next year.
Despite the fact that the toll road will be opened to traffic at the end of 2014, it is not expected that the construction will be completed before 2016.
The tunnel began to be designed in 2005.
It will have two double tracks, an electronic toll system and a complex ventilation system.
The Queensland Government will provide A$500 million (€308 million) for its funding.
Brisbane already has jobs for Hochtief .
